Ozo, one of the housemates of Big Brother Naija Lockdown, has prayed for former housemates following the conclusion of the reunion on Friday. He took to his Instagram Story on Saturday to say a prayer for each contestant as he also thanked fans and sponsors of the reality show. Ozo wrote, “To all of us; Laycon, our winner, your story and music would change the world. Dora, Your Business drive and enthusiasm would continue to take you across the globe. “Nengi, You are smart and hardworking, you are on a great path the world would see. Neo, May your energy continue to open doors for you across the globe. “Vee, from hearing the show to watching you host, your voice would be heard across the globe. Trikytee, Be you and we cannot wait to see the world through your lens. “Kidd, larger than life the world is yours. Prince, Mr Nigeria longest ever, you will carry that energy and do great things across the globe. “Tolani, May we see the world through your vlogs you have got this. Wathoni, You are an example to mothers across the world may they see you and learn. “Eric, May the world see the importance of being fit through your journey. Brighto, We sail the world through your stories without pressure. “Lucy, May we taste the goodness of your dishes across the world. Tochi, Show us brick by brick how we should build our life stories across the world.“ Ozo added, “Praise, may all your dance moves bring cultures and religions together across the world. Lilo, all your healthy meals keep us away from sickness. “Erica, your movies bring us to learn, love and laugh across the globe. Kaisha, every step you take teaches us to learn and love across the world. “Ka3na, May your drive for success be seen across the world.”